7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.035d3fa8-bdfe-4f16-a53e-81e325aaf883.prompt=User Identifier 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.197ade57-4319-403f-9323-5107ee6f5bed.description=
Service to perform HTTP PUT using the Java HTTP Client. This operation uploads a file or writes a string to the server location specified through the URL.

Inputs\:
    url - The URL to PUT from.
    username - The user name used for URL authentication. For NTLM authentication, the required format is 'domain\user'.
    password - The password used for URL authentication.
    authType - The type of authentication used by this operation when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, springForm, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
    kerberosConfFile - The  path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty, the "kdc" (Key Distribution Center) and "realm" get their values from the full domain name obtained from the web server URL.
    timeout - The time to wait for a connection to be established, in  milliseconds. 
Valid values\: This input needs a value greater than or equal to zero. A "timeout" value of 0 represents an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0
    socketTimeout - The time to wait for data to be retrieved, in milliseconds. 
Valid values\: This input needs a value greater than or equal to zero. A "socketTimeout" value of 0 represents an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0
    useCookies - Specifies whether to enable cookie tracking or not. Cookies are stored between consecutive calls. If you specify a non-Boolean value, the default value is used.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    proxy - The proxy server used to access the web site.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port.
Default value\: 8080
    proxyUsername - The proxy server user name.
    proxyPassword - The proxy server password associated with the "proxyUsername" input value.
    encodeURL - Specifies whether to encode the URL. If you specify a non-boolean value, the default value is used.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false
    file - The file to upload to the specified URL on the server.
    string - The string to write in the file found on the specified URL.
    userAgent - The value to use if the 'USER_AGENT' HTTP header has to be overwritten.
    trustAllRoots - Specifies whether to enable weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted certification authority issued it.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    x509HostnameVerifier - Specifies the way the server hostname must match a domain name in the subject's Common Name (CN) or subjectAltName field of the X.509 certificate. The hostname verification system prevents communication with other hosts other than the ones you intended. This is done by checking that the hostname is in the subject alternative name extension of the certificate. This system is designed to ensure that, if an attacker(Man In The Middle) redirects traffic to his machine, the client will not accept the connection. If you set this input to "allow_all", this verification is ignored and you become vulnerable to security attacks. For the value "browser_compatible" the hostname verifier works the same way as Curl and Firefox. The hostname must match either the first CN, or any of the subject-alts. A wildcard can occur in the CN, and in any of the subject-alts. The only difference between "browser_compatible" and "strict" is that a wildcard (such as "*.foo.com") with "browser_compatible" matches all subdomains, including "a.b.foo.com". From the security perspective, to provide protection against possible Man-In-The-Middle attacks, we strongly recommend to use "strict" option.
Default value\: allow_all
Valid values\: strict,browser_compatible,allow_all
    keystore - The location of the KeyStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS client authentication is used. The default value will be provided if "trustAllRoots" is "false".
Default value\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    keystorePassword - The password associated with the KeyStore file. If "trustAllRoots" is "false" and "keystore" is empty, "keystorePassword" default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    trustKeystore - The location of the TrustStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS server authentication is used. The default value will be provided if "trustAllRoots" is "false".
Default value\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    trustPassword - The password associated with the TrustStore file. If "trustAllRoots" is "false" and "trustKeystore" is empty, "trustPassword" default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    headerNamesList - The list containing the header names to use for the request.
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - The list containing the header values to use for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - The list containing the names of the query parameters to use for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2 
    queryValuesList - The list containing the values of the query parameters to use for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - The delimiter used to separates list elements.
Default value\: ','
    chunked - Chunked transfer encoding. By setting this parameter to "true" the operation will set HTTP Transfer-Encoding header to "chunked". 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true

Results\:
    returnCode - This is the primary output. A code used to determine the operation response, specifying whether the operation is successful or not.
    resultText - The raw result of the operation.
    document - The complete document returned by the Http Client Put operation.
    URL - The URL to PUT from.
    pageLoadTimeInMS - The time it took the page to load, in milliseconds.
    responseTimeInMS - The time it took the server to respond, in milliseconds.
    errorMessage - An informational message that can help determine the cause of error, if an error occurred.
    httpResult - The description of the HTTP response returned by the web server for the request sent by this operation. This result contains the HTTP response status or GENERAL_ERROR if the HTTP request could not be executed.
Examples\: SUCCESS, PAGE_NOT_FOUND, UNAUTHORIZED, FORBIDDEN and so on.
    responseHeaders - The list containing the headers of the response message, separated by "delimiter".
    status - The HTTP response code.
Example\: HTTP/1.1 200 OK

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Notes\:
1. You can use KeyTool to import a SSL certificate in a KeyStore. For example, to import a certificate in the Java cacerts KeyStore, run\: keytool -import -file c\:/../.cer -alias  -keystore /java/lib/security/cacerts -keystorepass changeit. If the KeyStore does not exist, the command tries to create a new one containing only your certificate.
2. You can use KeyTool to create a certificate chain through the following command\: 
   keytool -genkey -dname "cn\=Mark Jones, ou\=JavaSoft, o\=Sun, c\=US" 
      -alias business -keypass kpi135 -keystore C\:\working\mykeystore 
      -storepass ab987c -validity 180
This creates a certificate chain in a new KeyStore containing only one certificate. It is useful in SSL client authentication because the KeyManager ignores any certificates not included in a certificate chain.
3. If the value assigned to the "trustAllRoots" input is "false" and "trustKeystore" is empty, the operation tries to use the default trust store, using the password "changeit". 
4. If the authentication type is Kerberos, you might need to add an SPN (Service Principal Name) for the web server's computer account.  In order to do this, you can use ADUC (Active Directory Users and Computers) with enabled 'Advanced Features'. Go to the web server's computer account (example\: CN\=,CN\=Computers,DC\=domain,DC\=com), open the 'Properties' window and press the 'Attribute Editor' tab. Observe the values of the 'servicePrincipalName' attribute and add your SPN if not present. For example, HTTP/\:port.
5. After running any HTTP Client operation with "trustAllRoots" set to "true", the system ignores this input for all subsequent runs until you restart the RSJRAS. This means that it accepts any client or server certificate whether you set "trustAllRoots" to "false" and "trustKeystore" to a valid KeyStore file.
6. If you need to specify the request header fields, use the "headerNamesList" and "headerValuesList" inputs. The operation also accepts hidden inputs whose names begin with "header_", but this deprecated. You can add multiple headers.  For example, add an input name called "header_Content-Type" with a "text/html" value and/or an input name called "header_Content-Length" with a "348" value.  The operation strips off the "header_" prefix from the input name and then creates the "Content-Type" and/or "Content-Length" header with the value you specified. If you specify the same header through both the "headerNamesList" and the "header_" hidden inputs, the used value is the one from the "headerValuesList" list, and not from the hidden input.
7. If you need to specify query parameters when making the request, use the "queryNamesList" and "queryValuesList" inputs. The operation also accepts including query parameters in the URL. For example, http\://hostname\:80/page.asp?parameterName1\=parameterValue1¶meterName2\=parameterValue2. If you specify the same query parameter both through the "queryNamesList" and the "url" inputs, the used value is the one from the "queryValuesList", not the one included in the URL.
8. Apache Tomcat is currently the only supported application server when using form-based authentication.
9. This operation uses chunked transfer encoding, which can cause failures when using HTTP servers and proxies that do not support HTTP/1.1 protocol.
10. The character encoding used for string input is UTF-8.

Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.4056f460-bd35-454e-a0ab-9cc58948a331.prompt=Process Instance ID 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.4b4758c2-e0f7-47e1-a170-6b2070b8d5bd.description=
This workflow returns the resource provider details.

Inputs-
providerId – Resource provider id
userIdentifier  - User Identifier id
authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
socketTimeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for the data to be retrieved. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A socketTimeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
useCookies - If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the Default value.
Default value\: true.
followRedirects - If true, the GET command automatically follows redirects. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true
proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - The port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
userAgent - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: true
keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client authentication is not to be used.
keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.
providerPassword - Don't provide any value to this input. This input is required by OO to  obfuscate the password through out the flow.

Outputs-
providerSAP – Provider access point
providerUser – Provider user name
providerPassword – Provider Password
7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.77ac4098-e4b7-4710-8e77-629e600fa1d4.prompt=86b8fde4-bad1-4432-86f0-b17a32da4d30.c55bb2bf-91db-4946-a946-dc7271a30546.prompt 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.7ea80ed8-b8ac-4768-bd84-3c027986435e.prompt=User Identifier 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.9534287c-d5dd-4366-aa3b-6a2b900f572d.prompt=User Identifier 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.98f7a54e-adcc-4326-863c-1807bda7eb11.prompt=Artifact ID 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.a8f28d64-5f36-4c4b-b412-760920023112.prompt=Resource Provider ID 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.b6fd7a31-86c8-4309-aaad-ce9cd4e130d7.prompt=User Identifier 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.bdd1b223-42b4-4b82-8c49-4bf0d852d0fc.prompt=User Identifier 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.d294ec4e-bf15-44b5-bc0b-fa38fa24a725.description=This workflow returns the component properties and values using Artifact APIs. result\: propertyNameValuesList\: pipe separated list of property name and values ( where each property name and values would be ; seprated and multiple values would be , seprated) e.g. - property 1; value1,value2|property 2; value3|property 3; value3,value4|........ 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.d7ef198a-3e54-4637-8ffe-39172fe37072.description=This workflow updates the Process Instance State using PEM API. Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State 7a2e3924-7a53-4491-bde4-0e279a1ccaf7.description=
Delete a exisitng User from VPC server, 

The creds must be passed in the xml request, so they are extracted from the resource provider
Calls the VPC  server webservice, and passes the action string deleteUser with username as parameters


Inputs Parameters\:

 CSA_CONTEXT_ID – CSA Context Id
 CSA_PROCESS_ID – CSA Process Instance Id
 SVC_COMPONENT_ID - This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID]
 RSC_PROVIDER_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL - This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL]
 RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time.
  		Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE - This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE]
 RSC_POOL_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID]
 SVC_INSTANCE_ID - This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 PRN_COMPONENT_ID – This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID]
 REQ_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID]
 REQ_USER_ID - This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID]
 USR_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID]
 RSC_BINDING_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID]

userid - existing user name in the VPC Server

Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.
